        <num>CCP 597</num>
        <heading>597.  Effect of judgment</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 597.  Effect of judgment
A definitive judgment on the merits rendered in a class action concludes all members of the class, whether joined in the action or not, if the members who were joined as parties fairly insured adequate representation of all members of the class.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112191</p>
        </authorialNote>
